      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PINCER MOVEMENT (2) handled the heavy conditions on debut, wining by 1.2L with ease over 1500m. He stayed strongly there and getting out in trip looks a good move with Pike sticking with him. Looks as though he'll stay all day and he can repeat the dose. WILD THINGS (3) is third-up here after tackling stronger company to begin this campaign, finishing 3L away most recently. Out to this trip though looks good as she just missed over 1700m before the break last campaign. Expecting a bold performance. ARIZONA SKY (1) bolted in two back before just a fair effort last start over 1650m here. An inside draw this time looks to suit him better and Cooper's claim comes in handy. Can get back to winning ways without surprising. ALL LACED UP (4) was too good over 1400m last start and can go close again out in distance. TAKE A LEAF (6) turned in a better run out to the mile last start and can improve again.",
